NAHCO Aviance and Turkish Airlines have signed a long – term contract and renewal of existing business pact reflecting the increasing confidence between the two organisations. The contract renewal would see the ground handling company handle all Turkish passenger and cargo flights and other ramp activities in all Turkish locations in Nigeria, including Lagos, Abuja, Kano and Port Harcourt. The renewal comes only a few weeks after the Company won the contract to handle Cabo Verde Airlines, the national airline of Cape Verde. Group Executive Director Commercial and Business Development, nahcoaviance, Prince Saheed Lasisi, said the decision ofthe partners to extend the agreement between them is a demonstration of the trust and confidence the parties have in each other. Lasisi said, “The fundamental of any relationship is trust. We have been in this relationship with Turkish for decades. Over this time, we have come to trust each other and to look out for what is in the best interest of one another.  We are proud to be chosen consistently over others because of our excellent service delivery and unparalleled customer experience.” NAHCO is West Africa’s leading ground handlingservice provider with presence in all major Nigerian Airports offering aircrafthandling, cargo handling, passenger handling, crew transportation, amongothers. Turkish Airlines to take delivery of 30 Boeing 787-9 Dreamliner aircraft ‘Why Turkish, Emirates airlines won’t fly Kano route soon’ Peacock, Turkish airline partner to boost cargo, airfreight